To rewrite a prototype function in SAPUI5, you can create your own controller that extends the `sap.ui.comp.personalization.BaseController` and override the `getTable2JsonTransient` function in your own controller. This way, the overridden function will only apply in your own app without affecting other apps.

Here is an example of how you can achieve this:

```javascript
sap.ui.define([
    "sap/ui/comp/personalization/BaseController"
], function(BaseController) {
    "use strict";

    return BaseController.extend("your.namespace.YourController", {

        getTable2JsonTransient: function(oControl, bReturnOnlyColumnsNotVisible, aExcludeColumnKeys) {
            // Custom implementation of getTable2JsonTransient function
            // Add your logic here

            // Call the original getTable2JsonTransient function from BaseController
            return BaseController.prototype.getTable2JsonTransient.call(this, oControl, bReturnOnlyColumnsNotVisible, aExcludeColumnKeys);
        }

    });

});
```

In this code snippet:
- `sap.ui.define` is used to define the module and its dependencies.
- `YourController` extends `BaseController` and overrides the `getTable2JsonTransient` function with your custom implementation.
- The custom implementation can include any additional logic or modifications specific to your app.
- The original `getTable2JsonTransient` function is called using `BaseController.prototype.getTable2JsonTransient.call(this, oControl, bReturnOnlyColumnsNotVisible, aExcludeColumnKeys)` to ensure the original functionality is maintained.

Make sure to replace `"your.namespace.YourController"` with your actual namespace and controller name.

By following this approach, you can customize the behavior of the `getTable2JsonTransient` function within your application without affecting other SAPUI5 applications that may be using the `BaseController` from the `sap.ui.comp.personalization` library.

To rewrite a prototype function from a SAPUI5 library such as `sap.ui.comp.personalization`, you can extend the base controller and override the desired function in your custom controller.

Here's an example of how you can achieve this:

1. First, create a custom controller by extending the `sap.ui.comp.personalization.BaseController`:

```JavaScript
sap.ui.define([
    "sap/ui/comp/personalization/BaseController"
], function(BaseController) {
    "use strict";

    return BaseController.extend("your.custom.namespace.CustomController", {
        metadata: {
            properties: {}
        },

        // override the getTable2JsonTransient function
        getTable2JsonTransient: function(oTable) {
            // your custom code here
            return {
                // your custom JSON result
            };
        }
    });
});
```

2. In your application, when creating the personalization controller instance, use your custom controller instead of the base controller:

```JavaScript
var oPersonalizationController = new your.custom.namespace.CustomController();

// Use the personalization controller as usual
oPersonalizationController.getTable2JsonTransient(oTable);
```

By following these steps, you have successfully rewritten the `getTable2JsonTransient` function in your custom controller without affecting other applications. Your custom implementation will now be used in your specific app where the custom controller is instantiated.

