If the function `getTable2JsonTransient` is being called by another module in your application, you can still override the function in your custom controller by modifying the prototype of the `sap.ui.comp.personalization.BaseController`.

Here's how you can achieve this:

```JavaScript
sap.ui.define([
    "sap/ui/comp/personalization/BaseController"
], function(BaseController) {
    "use strict";

    var CustomController = BaseController.extend("your.custom.namespace.CustomController", {
        getTable2JsonTransient: function(oTable) {
            // Your custom implementation here
            return {
                // Your custom JSON result
            };
        }
    });

    // Override the original BaseController's prototype function
    CustomController.prototype.getTable2JsonTransient = function(oTable) {
        // Your custom implementation here
        return {
            // Your custom JSON result
        };
