In Flutter, you can use a `Column` with two children, and the first child takes up as much space as it needs, while the second child takes up the remaining space. Here's how you can achieve this:

```dart
Column(
  children: [
    // First child takes up as much space as needed
    Text(
      'This is the first child',
      style: TextStyle(fontSize: 20),
    ),
    // Second child takes up the remaining space
    Expanded(
      child: Container(
        color: Colors.blue,
        child: Center(
          child: Text(
            'This is the second child',
            style: TextStyle(fontSize: 20, color: Colors.white),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    ),
  ],
);
```
In this example, the `Text` widget is the first child of the `Column`, and it takes up as much space as it needs based on the length of the text. The `Expanded` widget is the second child, and it takes up the remaining space. Inside the `Expanded` widget is a `Container` that has a blue background color, and a `Center` widget with the second `Text` widget that is colored white.
